Real estate developer Cytonn Real Estate has opened three new offices in Nairobi as the firm seeks to increase its footprint in the country.The firm which has over Sh74 billion in real estate projects under its mandate yesterday opened an office at the Alma, a comprehensive lifestyle development project in Ruaka. Other offices are at Fedha Plaza located in Westlands and a Site Office in Karen. &ldquo;Our deal pipeline serves the various segments of the market ranging from the high end, such as the Amara Ridge in Karen, which is 100 per cent sold three-months to completion, to the middle to lower-middle income such as the Alma, which will offer a comprehensive lifestyle and a secure community to future families,&rdquo; Cytonn chief investment officer Elizabeth Nkukuu said.